{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17629408","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17629408"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:07:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:07:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17282"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17282","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17282"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0.17,0.78,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9972"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76972"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9972","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9972"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17282"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62477"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7166"},{"type":"tags","id":"7173"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23360"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23362"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76972","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76972"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDermatomes are specific areas of skin that are innervated by sensory fibers from a single spinal nerve root. Understanding dermatomes is crucial for diagnosing and localising neurological conditions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following clinically important dermatomes is located at the T10 level?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Groin region","Genitalia","Nipples","Umbilicus","Anus"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe T10 dermatome is located at the level of the \u003Cstrong\u003Eumbilicus\u003C/strong\u003E. This is a clinically important landmark for assessing sensory nerve function and diagnosing conditions such as shingles or spinal cord injuries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGroin region\u003C/strong\u003E - This is associated with the L1 dermatome\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenitalia\u003C/strong\u003E - This is associated with the S2-S4 dermatomes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENipples\u003C/strong\u003E - This is associated with the T4 dermatome\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnus\u003C/strong\u003E - This is associated with the S5 dermatome\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the distribution of dermatomes helps in localising neurological lesions and assessing nerve damage.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The T10 dermatome corresponds to the level of the umbilicus.","Dermatomes are areas of skin innervated by sensory fibers from a single spinal nerve root.","Knowledge of dermatomes is important for diagnosing and localising neurological conditions."],"references":["Kaiser JT, Lugo-Pico JG. Neuroanatomy, Spinal Nerves. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK542218/","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons."]},"relationships":{"itemRe